</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org85563f2">
<h2 id="org85563f2">Constant-sum vs non-constant-sum games</h2>
<ul>
<li>Constant sum
<ul>
<li>The sum total payoffs are fixed</li>
<li>Playing the game only determines the allocation of payoffs, not the total amount</li>

</ul></li>
<li>Zero sum
<ul>
<li>A special case of constant sum where total payoffs are zero</li>
<li>Often used to refer to constant-sum games</li>

</ul></li>
<li>Non-constant sum
<ul>
<li>Total payoffs depend on choices of players</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>

</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org9119ae5">
<h2 id="org9119ae5">Nim</h2>
<p>
Constant or non-constant sum?
</p>
<ul>
<li class="fragment appear"><i>constant (zero)</i></li>

</ul>

</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orgeed1083">
